snippet.title: Matt Steffanina
snippet.description:
Hey guys, thanks for checking out my channel.  I moved to LA 10 years ago to pursue my dreams of becoming a professional dancer and DJ.  Thanks to you guys so many of those dreams have come true from dancing on shows such as So You Think You Can Dance, Step Up, Ellen, and worked with artists like Taylor Swift, Jason Derulo and Meghan Trainor.

I also have an Online Dance Academy called DNCR (www.dncr.com) where me and my dancers teach people like you how to dance.  We have courses for brand new beginners all the way up through professional level, so if you've ever wanted to try dancing make sure you check out the website!

ps - you can find me on social media @MattSteffanina

The first time I watched this waaaaaaay back, I didn't know who to look at cos they are all great!
Fast forward to 2020, I still don't know who to look at cos they are all great. I kinda miss seeing all them (and the other kids) dance together though.


I see Tati on IG and her makeup is always outstanding (missing her with Tahani and Kaycee.. the golden trio). <3
Bailey now choreographed for a kpop group from her motherland (yass you go girl. I love Psycho). <3
Sean editing his own awesome videos (and seeing him mostly with Kaycee) and choreographing out of this world creations! <3
Kenneth visiting and joining a show in his motherland (together with AC) <3
Gabe performing with BTS and does collab with AC as well <3


These kids had gone a loooooong way now and Ifeel so proud seeing them in their own zones. <3 Okay, I'll stop this long post before I go emotional like a mom. HAHAHA.
